<div id="review_4001574842" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4001574842" />
    <a title="Kyra Leseberg (Roots &amp; Reads)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5899398-kyra-leseberg-roots-reads"><img alt="Kyra Leseberg (Roots &amp; Reads)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1523718393p2/5899398.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4001574842?book_show_action=true">May 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kyra Leseberg (Roots &amp; Reads)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kyra Leseberg (Roots &amp; Reads)" href="/user/show/5899398-kyra-leseberg-roots-reads">Kyra Leseberg (Roots &amp; Reads)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4001574842" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15523439768800478379">A small town is rocked by the discovery of a child’s body buried haphazardly near the road. When police zero-in on a nearby felon recently released from prison, he’s nowhere to be found. A search of his property yields a horrifying discovery: the bodies of more than 20 children, some buried for decades. The FBI is called in to investigate and help locate their suspect.<br/>College professor Eric Evans is new in town and nursing a broken heart. He begins to hallucinate a young boy - what he believes t</span>
  <span id="freeText15523439768800478379" style="display:none">A small town is rocked by the discovery of a child’s body buried haphazardly near the road. When police zero-in on a nearby felon recently released from prison, he’s nowhere to be found. A search of his property yields a horrifying discovery: the bodies of more than 20 children, some buried for decades. The FBI is called in to investigate and help locate their suspect.<br />College professor Eric Evans is new in town and nursing a broken heart. He begins to hallucinate a young boy - what he believes to be a symptom of his medication-managed schizophrenia. It’s isn’t long before the visions become terrifying and seem somehow linked to an old steamer trunk Eric recently found and restored.<br />Officer Susan Marlan cannot sit idly by while the FBI takes over this case; she has an idea of the identity of the first body that was discovered - and is stunned when Eric comes forward with a story that seems to back up her theory. Together they work to uncover the truth behind the horrifying body farm.<br /><br />There was a lot of time spent on Eric’s messy divorce that had absolutely nothing to do with the story; it was simply filler. The pace was off: first half is mostly filler, it’s not until the halfway mark that Eric and Susan actually meet, they jump straight to interviewing one person together, the truth becomes glaringly obvious, and then we rush to an extremely predictable double twist (no shock on either) ending. While I liked that this book blended the supernatural with a murder mystery, it had trouble holding my attention so I’m unlikely to continue with this series.<br /><br />For more reviews, visit <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.rootsandreads.wordpress.com">www.rootsandreads.wordpress.com</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="15523439768800478379" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


