<div id="review_3145400302" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3145400302" />
    <a title="Christa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/261662-christa"><img alt="Christa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1524003029p2/261662.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3145400302?book_show_action=true">Jan 16, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Christa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Christa" href="/user/show/261662-christa">Christa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/261662-christa?shelf=kindle-unlimited">kindle-unlimited</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3145400302" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7381471300739964953">This was a very good suspense/thriller with a few creepy moments! Those were provided by the paranormal elements of the story. I thought this one had an engaging storyline, and it sure kept me interested! I quickly became invested in the two main characters, Susan and Eric, and kept wanting their storylines to hurry and intersect! I thought both were great characters, and I liked the way that Eric&apos;s mental illness was handled in a way that didn&apos;t diminish him as a character.<br/><br/>Even though there wer</span>
  <span id="freeText7381471300739964953" style="display:none">This was a very good suspense/thriller with a few creepy moments! Those were provided by the paranormal elements of the story. I thought this one had an engaging storyline, and it sure kept me interested! I quickly became invested in the two main characters, Susan and Eric, and kept wanting their storylines to hurry and intersect! I thought both were great characters, and I liked the way that Eric's mental illness was handled in a way that didn't diminish him as a character.<br /><br />Even though there were some things that were obvious from the beginning, the storyline is complex, and continues on past those predictable points. I'm very much looking forward to the next book!</span>
  <a data-text-id="7381471300739964953" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

