  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3667817392" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3667817392" />
    <a title="Benjamin Thomas" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4209082-benjamin-thomas"><img alt="Benjamin Thomas" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1451660582p2/4209082.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3667817392?book_show_action=true">Nov 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Benjamin Thomas" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Benjamin Thomas" href="/user/show/4209082-benjamin-thomas">Benjamin Thomas</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4209082-benjamin-thomas?shelf=mystery-amateur-sleuth">mystery-amateur-sleuth</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4209082-benjamin-thomas?shelf=thriller-cops-feds">thriller-cops-feds</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3667817392" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15740526712285873035">The first in the “Dead Remaining” series features two protagonists: Susan, a well-regarded up-and-coming cop and Eric, a college professor who suffers from schizophrenia. They each have interesting back stories (especially refreshing to have a schizophrenic as a good guy) and eventually meet each other during the larger plot which involves the grisly discovery of over twenty graves on a farm outside of town. The meaning behind the series’ title becomes apparent about a quarter of the way through</span>
  <span id="freeText15740526712285873035" style="display:none">The first in the “Dead Remaining” series features two protagonists: Susan, a well-regarded up-and-coming cop and Eric, a college professor who suffers from schizophrenia. They each have interesting back stories (especially refreshing to have a schizophrenic as a good guy) and eventually meet each other during the larger plot which involves the grisly discovery of over twenty graves on a farm outside of town. The meaning behind the series’ title becomes apparent about a quarter of the way through this first book but I won’t provide that spoiler in this review.<br /><br />Based on this first novel in the series, I feel comfortable in praising the author’s writing skills. She can paint the proverbial word picture very well and invoke emotional characterizations. She also manages to adroitly balance the mystery and thriller aspects. I am aware that she has written other books under a different name but if she hasn’t yet tried for a true horror novel, I would urge her to give it a whirl. The suspenseful narration on display in this one should serve that goal well.<br /><br />Unfortunately, I can’t praise the plot development in the same way. The mystery elements seemed to be aiming for surprise twists, but they were blatantly obvious. The identity of the big bad was clear from the very first clue, as was the surprise reveal near the end. Just too predictable.<br /><br />Still, I would be interested in reading the second book to see where events take these two characters. I just won’t be in a hurry to do so.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15740526712285873035" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

